So the `onUpdate` function takes `{ content, details }` — which is exactly what the orchestrator code does. The framework should be picking this up and calling `renderResult({ isPartial: true })`.

Let me look at the tool-execution.ts source to understand the rendering flow. Actually, let me look at the `tool-execution.ts` file referenced in the docs.

Wait, actually let me re-read the user's bug report more carefully:

> "The renderResult({ isPartial: true }) fix might not be working. The tool just showed the final result without showing progress during execution."

This means the `renderResult` with `isPartial: true` IS being implemented but the activity feed isn't showing. Let me check if there's a timing issue or if `onUpdate` is actually being called.

Looking at the orchestrator code more carefully:

```typescript
onUpdate?.({
    content: [{ type: "text", text: `⠋ ${specialist.name}...` }],
    details: { status: "running", specialist: specialist.name },
});

const result = await runSubagent(specialist, params.task, ctx.cwd, { modelRegistry: ctx.modelRegistry, model: ctx.model }, signal, onUpdate);
```

This calls `onUpdate` once before `runSubagent`, then passes `onUpdate` to `runSubagent`.

Inside `runSubagent`, `onUpdate` is called in the `session.subscribe` handler:

```typescript
const unsubscribe = session.subscribe((event) => {
    if (event.type === "message_update" && event.assistantMessageEvent.type === "text_delta") {
        output += event.assistantMessageEvent.delta;
        parseTextForFeed(feed, event.assistantMessageEvent.delta);
    }
    if (event.type === "message_end" && event.message?.role === "assistant") {
        turns++;
        // ...
        onUpdate?.({
            content: [{ type: "text", text }],
            details: { specialist: specialist.name, status: "running", turns },
        });
    }
    if (event.type === "tool_call") {
        // ...
        onUpdate?.({...});
    }
    if (event.type === "tool_result") {
        // ...
        onUpdate?.({...});
    }
});
```

So `onUpdate` IS being called multiple times during execution. The question is: why isn't the TUI showing the partial results?

